<dl id="n10076g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10076g">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10076g"> 76(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> &frac12; scytale completes / other</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">H&eacute;rod. &ldquo;Les &eacute;phores de Sparte communiquaient avec les rois et les g&eacute;n&eacute;raux en campagne, &agrave; l&apos;aide de la <mark>scytala</mark>, b&acirc;ton entour&eacute; d&apos;une bande de cuir sur laquelle ils &eacute;crivaient leurs ordres. Cette bande d&eacute;roul&eacute;e ne pr&eacute;sentait que des caract&egrave;res sans suite, mais le g&eacute;n&eacute;ral <mark>en retrouvait l&apos;ordre &agrave; l&apos;aide d&apos;une scytale semblable</mark> qu&apos;il portait avec lui.&rdquo; <font color="green">[Herod. &ldquo;The magistrates of Sparta communicated with the kings and generals in the field with the scytale, a stick surrounded by a leather band on which they wrote their orders. This band once unrolled only revealed disconnected characters but the general could decode the order with a similar scytale which he carried with him.]</font> <small> Arthur de Rothschild, <a name="ARHD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ARHD"><cite title="source">Histoire de la poste</cite></a> (1876) 27f</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
